      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model form selection must be justified by literature precedent and sensitivity analysis demonstrating that simplifying assumptions (e.g., isotropic Ti-6Al-4V, frictionless rod-screw interface) do not change QoI by more than 5%.",
      "rationale": "Isotropic linear-elastic Ti-6Al-4V (E=114 GPa, nu=0.33) is well-supported by published implant FEA literature. Sensitivity study varying friction coefficient (0.0 to 0.3) showed <3% change in stiffness QoI. Model form level 3 achieved and required."
